article.headline: San Jose St. 83, Hawaii 60
article.story: SAN JOSE, Calif. -- Adrian Oliver had 33 points, Chris Oakes matched his season high with 18 points and nine rebounds and San Jose State built a big lead in the second half then coasted to an 83-60 win over Hawaii on Thursday night. Oliver, the reigning Western Athletic Conference player of the week after leading the Spartans to impressive home wins over first-place Louisiana Tech and New Mexico State, went 12 of 18 from the floor and made all three of his 3-point attempts. San Jose State (12-8, 5-3 WAC), which lost to Hawaii 68-67 on Jan. 17, led by as much as 27. The Spartans are 9-1 at the Events Center, their best home record since going 10-0 to start the 1980-81 season. Roderick Flemings had 19 points for the Warriors (9-12, 2-6), which lost its third straight. The Warriors remained winless on the road and haven't won away from home since beating Fresno State 73-69 on Feb. 19, 2009.
